div.p:
2. The foundation hereinabove referred to should be administered by internationally known United States and Latin American citizens for the benefit of the Dominican people. Tentatively, the following names have been suggested for trustees:
Ex-Presidents Hoover and Truman of the United States;The phrase, “President Eisenhower after 1961,”was lined out by the President at this point in the source text.
Ex-President Eduardo Santos of Colombia;
Ex-President Galo Plaza of Ecuador;
President Kubitschek of Brazil (whose term expires this year);
Pedro Aramburu, former Provisional President of Argentina;
Ex-President Ruiz Cortines of Mexico; possibly Raphael Trujillo himself.
